40:  * being allocated to has enough disk space.
41:  *
42:  * It has the following configurable settings, all of which can be changed dynamically:
43:  *
44:  * <code>cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low</code> is the low disk
45:  * watermark. New shards will not allocated to a node with usage higher than this,
46:  * although this watermark may be passed by allocating a shard. It defaults to
47:  * 0.85 (85.0%).
48:  *
49:  * <code>cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.low.max_headroom</code> is the
50:  * max headroom for the low watermark. Defaults to 200GB when the low watermark
51:  * is not explicitly set. This caps the amount of free space required.
52:  *
53:  * <code>cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high</code> is the high disk
54:  * watermark. If a node has usage higher than this, shards are not allowed to
55:  * remain on the node. In addition, if allocating a shard to a node causes the
56:  * node to pass this watermark, it will not be allowed. It defaults to
57:  * 0.90 (90.0%).
58:  *
59:  * <code>cluster.routing.allocation.disk.watermark.high.max_headroom</code> is the
60:  * max headroom for the high watermark. Defaults to 150GB when the high watermark
61:  * is not explicitly set. This caps the amount of free space required.
62:  *
63:  * The watermark settings are expressed in terms of used disk percentage/ratio, or
